911 dispatch.

00:41.554 --> 00:43.622
What's the emergency?

00:43.624 --> 00:45.957
There's been an accident.

00:45.959 --> 00:48.293
What's the location?

00:48.295 --> 00:50.128
9 Summit Street.

00:54.101 --> 00:56.302
Sugar.

00:56.304 --> 01:00.574
I call my baby my sugar.

01:00.576 --> 01:04.944
I never maybe my sugar.

01:04.947 --> 01:11.754
That's 'cause my baby's
so confectionary.

01:11.756 --> 01:17.993
Funny, he never
asks for my money,

01:17.995 --> 01:22.466
'long as I feed him on honey.

01:22.468 --> 01:24.767
That he can get anytime.

01:24.769 --> 01:27.103
Walter!

01:27.105 --> 01:28.972
I'm making breakfast.

01:35.615 --> 01:37.348
You want French toast?

01:37.350 --> 01:39.251
I'm making French toast!

02:34.251 --> 02:34.815
Hey!

02:34.817 --> 02:36.151
Hey, are you OK?

02:47.399 --> 02:49.364
Like that.

02:49.366 --> 02:51.835
Try it again.

02:54.306 --> 02:55.405
Excuse me.

02:55.407 --> 02:56.941
Ms. Olson, you have a call.

02:56.943 --> 02:57.976
It's one of your neighbors.

02:57.978 --> 02:59.143
It happened so fast.

02:59.145 --> 03:00.977
Where were you?

03:00.979 --> 03:02.947
I was home, working in
my yard just over there.

03:02.949 --> 03:05.282
Over there.

03:05.284 --> 03:06.417
Tough pendejo, though, huh?

03:06.419 --> 03:08.588
Step right in front of a car.

03:08.590 --> 03:09.922
I thought for sure
when I ran down here,

03:09.924 --> 03:11.656
he'd be in bad shape, but...

03:11.658 --> 03:13.226
You know him?

03:13.228 --> 03:13.827
Uh, not so much.

03:13.829 --> 03:16.062
Just a wave.

03:16.064 --> 03:18.965
You know Wren Miller,
17B Green Street?

03:18.967 --> 03:21.969
She reported the accident.

03:21.971 --> 03:24.472
Never heard of her.

03:51.406 --> 03:51.971
Police!

03:51.973 --> 03:52.806
Anybody home?

04:06.389 --> 04:06.921
Hello?

04:06.923 --> 04:08.289
Miss Miller?

05:53.980 --> 05:55.478
Young lady!

05:55.480 --> 05:56.714
Hey!

05:56.716 --> 06:00.985
27 hours I have been getting
on and off the airplane.

06:00.987 --> 06:04.656
It's 27 hours.

06:05.425 --> 06:06.892
Why are your eyes puffy?

06:06.894 --> 06:09.262
Have you been eating?

06:09.264 --> 06:10.965
Don't you start with me.

06:14.571 --> 06:16.671
See, this is why the
doctor said you should get

06:16.673 --> 06:17.938
up every two hours and walk.

06:17.940 --> 06:19.572
I like to sit.

06:19.574 --> 06:22.043
Well, he wants you to
talk so you keep the blood

06:22.045 --> 06:23.211
flowing in your veins.

06:23.213 --> 06:25.781
My blood is flowing, Jo Jo.

06:25.783 --> 06:28.317
It's my joints who
won't cooperate.

06:28.319 --> 06:30.019
How are your joints, Donna?

06:30.021 --> 06:31.288
My joints are great.

06:31.290 --> 06:32.255
They're cooperating?

06:32.257 --> 06:33.690
My joints are cooperating.

06:33.692 --> 06:35.158
I bet they are.

06:37.062 --> 06:38.195
So how are things?

06:38.197 --> 06:39.562
Well, Mr. Lemke
tried to kill himself.

06:39.564 --> 06:40.432
Oh, no.

06:40.434 --> 06:41.598
Not again.

06:41.600 --> 06:42.700
Poor Margaret.

06:42.702 --> 06:44.702
Mr. Lemke is
a horse's ass, Jo Jo.

06:44.704 --> 06:45.803
Yes.

06:45.805 --> 06:47.305
I... I've told
her a thousand times.

06:47.307 --> 06:48.740
Well, why does
he keep doing that?

06:48.742 --> 06:51.678
He's gonna die soon enough
as it is without sending

06:51.680 --> 06:53.546
Margaret into hysterics.

06:53.548 --> 06:54.613
I know.

06:54.615 --> 06:55.748
It's just terrible.

06:55.750 --> 06:56.548
We should go over there.

06:56.550 --> 06:57.817
No.

06:57.819 --> 06:58.651
No, he's fine.

06:58.653 --> 07:00.353
They took him to the hospital.

07:00.355 --> 07:02.656
Not a nice welcome
for my new tenant,

07:02.658 --> 07:04.159
but what are you gonna do?

07:04.161 --> 07:05.860
You found someone
to take the apartment?

07:05.862 --> 07:06.360
Yeah.

07:06.362 --> 07:07.161
Single?

07:07.163 --> 07:07.995
- Stop it.
- Male?

07:07.997 --> 07:09.130
Female?

07:09.132 --> 07:11.767
I don't know anything
about the young lady.

07:11.769 --> 07:12.534
Uh-huh?

07:12.536 --> 07:14.235
And I don't want to know.

07:14.237 --> 07:17.106
You become less fun
the longer I know you.

07:17.108 --> 07:18.007
Thank you so much!

07:18.009 --> 07:21.846
Is she home?

07:21.848 --> 07:23.514
I think she's home.

07:23.516 --> 07:24.815
Why don't we get you home?

07:24.817 --> 07:26.416
Yeah, all right.

07:26.418 --> 07:27.452
OK?

07:27.454 --> 07:29.387
Arnie,
where are you going?

07:29.389 --> 07:30.988
We have a whole car to unload.

07:30.990 --> 07:33.091
Well, if I lift anything,
my arm'll fall off.

07:34.362 --> 07:37.096
I've been married to
that man for 41 years.

07:37.098 --> 07:38.298
I know.

07:38.300 --> 07:41.466
And I don't think he's
ever carried his suitcase.

09:37.203 --> 09:41.705
I can see this is me.

09:41.707 --> 09:44.007
I will be.

09:44.009 --> 09:46.878
You'll all see I'm the one.

09:56.525 --> 09:57.959
Oh, sorry.

09:57.961 --> 09:58.925
You are way too happy.

09:58.927 --> 10:00.962
There's no such thing.

10:00.964 --> 10:01.662
I get to be outside.

10:01.664 --> 10:03.931
I... I get to exercise.

10:03.933 --> 10:04.800
I get to meet people.

10:04.802 --> 10:06.068
I get a...

10:06.070 --> 10:06.736
A pension.

10:06.738 --> 10:08.036
I get a pension.

10:08.038 --> 10:08.871
Health care.

10:08.873 --> 10:10.006
I get health care.

10:10.008 --> 10:10.805
Vacations.

10:10.807 --> 10:11.306
See?

10:11.308 --> 10:12.275
Who knows?

10:12.277 --> 10:13.709
But wait, job lover.

10:13.711 --> 10:14.577
There's more.

10:17.582 --> 10:20.084
Goes to one address.

10:20.086 --> 10:21.819
Huh.

10:21.821 --> 10:22.219
Whoa.

10:25.557 --> 10:27.458
You missed a spot.

10:50.320 --> 10:50.719
He's back.

10:54.524 --> 10:56.025
Would you stop?

10:56.027 --> 10:57.060
Shh.

10:57.062 --> 10:58.127
Arnie.

10:58.129 --> 10:59.027
What?

10:59.029 --> 11:00.630
They can't hear me.

11:03.735 --> 11:05.936
She's leaving him.

11:05.938 --> 11:08.607
Gotta be the smartest
thing she's ever done.

11:08.609 --> 11:11.175
Huh.

11:11.177 --> 11:13.079
Look at that.

11:13.081 --> 11:15.848
He is just sitting
there in his front yard.

11:15.850 --> 11:17.181
So?

11:17.183 --> 11:20.419
We're just sitting
here in our front yard.

11:20.421 --> 11:21.354
Do you need anything?

11:25.860 --> 11:27.228
I'm going over there.

11:27.230 --> 11:29.829
Jo... what?

11:29.831 --> 11:32.099
Are you taking your chair?

11:32.101 --> 11:32.767
Yes!

11:32.769 --> 11:34.469
I'm taking my chair.

12:06.140 --> 12:07.574
Holy cow.

12:07.576 --> 12:09.142
Hey, Mr. B.

12:09.144 --> 12:11.344
What are you bringing
me there, baby pigs?

12:11.346 --> 12:14.415
No, it's
actually not for you.

12:14.417 --> 12:17.017
Goes up there.

12:17.019 --> 12:19.588
Where's Jo Ann?

12:19.590 --> 12:21.490
She's found another man.

12:25.062 --> 12:34.537
Hello, Walt. Oh, my.

12:34.539 --> 12:35.438
This is nice.

12:55.730 --> 12:56.965
Pygmy Falcon.

12:59.668 --> 13:01.802
Yes, it... it is.

13:01.804 --> 13:02.969
I'm Wren.

13:02.971 --> 13:05.839
I moved in while the
two of you were away.

13:05.841 --> 13:07.209
Ah.

13:07.211 --> 13:14.951
Well, uh... I don't remember
seeing this when I was there.

13:14.953 --> 13:18.155
I mean, I didn't see...

13:18.157 --> 13:22.026
I know I didn't see it.

13:22.028 --> 13:25.230
But here it is.

13:25.232 --> 13:27.632
Oh, I'm Arnie.

13:27.634 --> 13:29.035
Arnie Bayberry.

13:29.037 --> 13:31.036
Nice to meet you.

13:31.038 --> 13:31.536
Careful.

13:31.538 --> 13:32.171
Whoa.

13:32.173 --> 13:32.871
Watch your birds.

13:37.513 --> 13:38.478
How was Africa?

13:38.480 --> 13:39.813
It was good.

13:39.815 --> 13:42.282
You didn't go out and find a
girlfriend while I was gone,

13:42.284 --> 13:43.884
did you?

13:43.886 --> 13:44.853
Uh, no.

13:44.855 --> 13:46.286
No, ma'am.

13:46.288 --> 13:47.154
Still single.

13:50.293 --> 13:53.028
Oh.

13:53.030 --> 13:54.298
That must be here.

13:57.735 --> 14:00.103
Oh, she's lovely, isn't she?

14:00.105 --> 14:02.738
She's just lovely.

14:02.740 --> 14:03.706
Who is she?

14:03.708 --> 14:05.443
My new neighbor.

14:05.445 --> 14:07.111
The one who
lives above the garage?

14:07.113 --> 14:09.381
Yeah.

14:09.383 --> 14:12.984
I should go introduce
myself to her.

14:12.986 --> 14:15.555
She gets a lot of mail.

14:15.557 --> 14:18.424
Hello, hello, hello.

14:18.426 --> 14:20.092
Oh, look at you.

14:20.094 --> 14:22.162
You are just lovely.

14:22.164 --> 14:24.730
I almost stopped
by this morning,

14:24.732 --> 14:26.901
but my husband told me not
to knock on anybody's doors

14:26.903 --> 14:28.903
- until 9:00 AM.
- Hi.

14:28.905 --> 14:30.103
I'm Wren.

14:30.105 --> 14:30.805
Hi.

14:30.807 --> 14:33.041
Oh, wow, look at that.

14:33.043 --> 14:35.711
Where in the world are you
going with all of that?

14:39.583 --> 14:41.916
Oh, my.

14:41.918 --> 14:44.954
Isn't it a beautiful day?

14:44.956 --> 14:47.723
I live right next to you
with my husband Arnie.

14:47.725 --> 14:49.392
I was just mentioning to Josh.

14:49.394 --> 14:53.263
He's the nice young mailman over
there, sitting with Mr. Lemke.

14:53.265 --> 14:54.164
Let's wave.

14:59.506 --> 15:00.540
Josh is single.

15:00.542 --> 15:03.575
His mother died last
year, poor thing.

15:03.577 --> 15:05.012
And he was there the whole time.

15:05.014 --> 15:06.647
They don't get any
better than that.

15:06.649 --> 15:08.915
He's the real deal.

15:08.917 --> 15:11.050
Are you single?

15:11.052 --> 15:12.752
Here, let's walk.

15:12.754 --> 15:15.455
I can tell you all you need to
know about this neighborhood,

15:15.457 --> 15:17.959
but today I'm kind
of busy 'cause I have

15:17.961 --> 15:19.594
to keep my eyes on Mr. Lemke.

15:19.596 --> 15:23.666
It can be so bad sometimes
this whole getting older bit.

15:23.668 --> 15:27.371
But maybe later if you
want, I'll just stop by.

15:27.373 --> 15:28.906
What's your name again?

15:28.908 --> 15:29.940
Wren.

15:29.942 --> 15:31.141
Wren.

15:31.143 --> 15:33.611
Well, you are darn cute, Wren.

15:33.613 --> 15:36.147
Are you insane?

15:36.149 --> 15:37.882
Are you insane?
Hey!

15:37.884 --> 15:40.386
- Knock it off.
- Are you insane?

15:40.388 --> 15:43.153
Yes, definitely.

15:43.155 --> 15:44.156
Hey, Payne.

15:44.158 --> 15:45.924
You've been
blessed by a bird.

15:45.926 --> 15:46.326
Hm?

15:51.099 --> 15:51.797
Oh.

15:51.799 --> 15:52.799
No, come on, man.

15:52.801 --> 15:53.666
You should be happy.

15:53.668 --> 15:55.069
That's good luck.

15:55.071 --> 15:57.405
In fact, the next time you go
back out, why don't you pick me

15:57.407 --> 15:59.273
up $20 bucks in scratch-offs.

15:59.275 --> 16:04.213
And if I win, then
we'll split it 60-40.

16:04.215 --> 16:07.682
Maybe 50-50.

16:07.684 --> 16:08.318
OK.

16:08.320 --> 16:09.852
Take that as a no.

16:09.854 --> 16:11.387
Well, I'll take that
to your box, too.

16:12.625 --> 16:15.224
Or, you know, you
could go online.

16:15.226 --> 16:17.828
Blackjack, poker.
Trust me.

16:17.830 --> 16:18.829
This is a sign.

16:18.831 --> 16:20.765
Technology is overrated.

16:20.767 --> 16:21.531
Is it now?

16:21.533 --> 16:24.102
I was on this dating site.

16:24.104 --> 16:26.371
Met this woman for
drinks last week.

16:26.373 --> 16:27.406
Mm-hm?

16:27.408 --> 16:32.078
Matea from Oraro, Tonga.

16:34.250 --> 16:36.316
I'm telling you, man.

16:36.318 --> 16:39.020
There are all types
of people on there.

16:39.022 --> 16:40.153
What's it been, man?

16:40.155 --> 16:42.791
Six, seven years?

16:42.793 --> 16:44.192
This could be your jam.

16:48.264 --> 16:49.630
Here you go, Payne.

17:00.980 --> 17:02.813
A pygmy falcon?

17:02.815 --> 17:03.881
You're kidding.

17:03.883 --> 17:04.382
No, no.

17:04.384 --> 17:04.949
Really.

17:04.951 --> 17:05.782
Where is it?

17:05.785 --> 17:06.951
That's remarkable!

17:06.953 --> 17:08.487
Where'd you see it?

17:08.489 --> 17:09.286
Huh?

17:09.288 --> 17:10.321
Where'd you see it?

17:10.324 --> 17:12.324
You know, it's funny.

17:12.326 --> 17:13.859
I can't recall exactly.

17:13.862 --> 17:15.761
You can't recall?

17:15.762 --> 17:16.997
Arnie, you're a professional.

17:16.999 --> 17:19.266
You can't make claims
without proper verification.

17:19.268 --> 17:21.066
I'm not making a claim.

17:21.068 --> 17:23.469
This is just you and me talking.

17:23.471 --> 17:25.271
I don't mean to challenge you.

17:25.272 --> 17:27.107
I'm just surprised is all.

17:27.108 --> 17:27.940
I know.

17:27.942 --> 17:29.277
It's strange.

17:29.279 --> 17:32.279
All right, I just came across
the photo when I got back.

17:32.281 --> 17:35.084
I don't even remember taking it.

17:35.086 --> 17:37.152
Look, don't worry.

17:37.154 --> 17:41.658
Now I can't even find
the friggin' thing.

17:41.660 --> 17:46.163
Well, they are pretty small.

17:57.978 --> 17:59.944
Oh, thank goodness
you're home.

17:59.946 --> 18:01.614
Can I come in?

18:01.616 --> 18:02.649
Sure.

18:02.651 --> 18:03.883
It's for you.

18:03.885 --> 18:04.651
Go ahead.

18:04.653 --> 18:05.284
Open it.

18:05.286 --> 18:07.054
Oh.

18:07.056 --> 18:08.188
You didn't have to do that.

18:08.190 --> 18:08.590
Oh.

18:11.595 --> 18:13.595
- It's a meatball maker.
- Oh.

18:16.733 --> 18:17.565
OK, thanks.

18:17.567 --> 18:20.036
I ordered a ton of 'em on QVC.

18:20.038 --> 18:22.738
It's one of those
things everybody needs.

18:22.740 --> 18:24.307
You know how to work this?

18:24.309 --> 18:25.609
Um, well...

18:25.611 --> 18:29.645
See, you just spread the
seasoned meat on a counter,

18:29.647 --> 18:33.584
and then you press the plastic
gizmo down through the meat.

18:33.586 --> 18:36.554
Shake it around, open
it up, and voila.

18:36.556 --> 18:37.921
Perfect meatballs.

18:37.923 --> 18:38.957
It's amazing.

18:38.959 --> 18:40.359
You're gonna love it.

18:40.361 --> 18:42.061
I use mine all the time.

18:42.063 --> 18:43.429
Thank you.

18:43.431 --> 18:46.033
I'll just, um...

18:46.035 --> 18:48.168
I'll set it right here.

18:48.170 --> 18:48.568
Yeah.

18:51.507 --> 18:52.574
Wow.

18:52.576 --> 18:55.343
I thought only old
people still got mail.

18:55.345 --> 18:57.313
What do you do with it?

18:57.315 --> 18:58.446
I read it.

18:58.448 --> 18:59.547
Oh, don't be ridiculous.

18:59.549 --> 19:01.615
Nobody could read all this.

19:01.617 --> 19:02.883
Is it for work?

19:02.885 --> 19:03.853
What do you do?

19:03.855 --> 19:05.688
I... I really can't say.

19:05.690 --> 19:06.220
Oh, please.

19:06.222 --> 19:06.988
Don't worry.

19:06.990 --> 19:08.757
People tell me everything.

19:08.759 --> 19:10.693
I'm kind of like a priest.

19:10.695 --> 19:11.594
It's complicated.

19:11.596 --> 19:13.197
- It's complicated?
- It can be.

19:13.199 --> 19:18.569
Aways complicated, or is it
sometimes less complicated?

19:18.571 --> 19:20.037
Finally, a human.

19:20.039 --> 19:22.373
No, no, I'm not Caleb Murphy.

19:22.375 --> 19:23.709
That's the problem.

19:23.711 --> 19:24.843
My name is Moody Burkheart.

19:27.749 --> 19:29.815
B-U-R-K-heart.

19:29.817 --> 19:32.084
And something's gone
wrong with your system,

19:32.086 --> 19:35.889
because I'm not getting Caleb
Murphy's bill at my address.

19:35.891 --> 19:38.259
But I'm not getting my own bill.

19:46.538 --> 19:49.837
Uh, what?

19:49.839 --> 19:50.240
OK.

19:53.846 --> 19:58.115
So only Caleb Murphy can
make changes to this account.

19:58.117 --> 19:58.650
Uh-huh.

19:58.652 --> 20:00.151
It's policy.

20:00.153 --> 20:02.620
It's not policy.

20:02.622 --> 20:03.488
It's a mistake.

20:36.662 --> 20:38.728
I can't believe how
far along you are.

20:38.730 --> 20:41.196
Getting that lining
in was harder

20:41.198 --> 20:42.432
than building the casket.

20:42.434 --> 20:45.035
It's... it's...

20:45.037 --> 20:46.469
it's creepy.

20:46.471 --> 20:47.004
It's creepy!

20:48.909 --> 20:50.775
Arnie says it's creepy.

20:50.777 --> 20:52.343
It's... it's creepy.

20:52.345 --> 20:55.279
But it's no secret we're
all gonna die someday.

20:55.281 --> 20:56.748
Do you know how expensive it is?

20:56.750 --> 20:57.481
To die?

20:57.483 --> 20:59.419
Yeah, horribly expensive.

20:59.421 --> 21:01.453
$10,000 on average.

21:01.455 --> 21:03.757
It just makes me
sick to my stomach

21:03.759 --> 21:06.927
that just to lay a
person to rest families

21:06.929 --> 21:08.328
have to pay that kind of money.

21:08.330 --> 21:08.996
Hm.

21:08.998 --> 21:10.030
Oh!

21:10.032 --> 21:11.467
I can't believe I
forgot to tell you.

21:11.469 --> 21:12.399
I met Wren.

21:12.401 --> 21:14.902
She's a lovely
girl, just lovely.

21:14.904 --> 21:18.940
We had a great walk, and
I went to her house and...

21:18.942 --> 21:21.111
but did you know
about the mail thing?

21:21.113 --> 21:24.546
She gets hundreds, thousands
of letters every day.

21:24.548 --> 21:25.716
Hm.

21:25.718 --> 21:28.251
She must be some
sort of speed reader.

21:28.253 --> 21:29.385
Jo Ann.

21:29.387 --> 21:31.957
Anyway, I've been
thinking about it.

21:31.959 --> 21:34.726
Because, you know,
something is going on there,

21:34.728 --> 21:37.764
and I think I finally
figured it out.

21:37.766 --> 21:43.504
I am pretty sure she is
a pen pal for prisoners.

21:43.506 --> 21:44.403
A what?

21:44.405 --> 21:46.538
I'm talking lots of prisoners.

21:46.540 --> 21:49.142
You should see
these bags, and she

21:49.144 --> 21:50.442
doesn't want to talk about it.

21:50.444 --> 21:51.911
"It's complicated."

21:51.913 --> 21:52.746
Her words.

