43:12.353 --> 43:13.251
What's wrong?

43:13.253 --> 43:14.554
- Jo Jo!
- Please.

43:19.827 --> 43:21.595
Honey, no one's here.

43:21.597 --> 43:22.896
It's just me!

43:22.898 --> 43:26.101
What... what about Wren?

43:26.103 --> 43:29.070
Dear, Wren.

43:29.072 --> 43:30.838
From next door.

43:30.840 --> 43:31.673
No.

43:31.675 --> 43:32.275
No, hon.

43:32.277 --> 43:34.776
She's gone.

43:34.778 --> 43:37.581
She can't hear me.

43:37.583 --> 43:40.751
You just have to come down here.

43:40.753 --> 43:41.717
Yeah.

43:41.719 --> 43:42.653
No, come on.

43:42.655 --> 43:43.487
Oh, OK.

43:50.929 --> 43:52.163
Honey, I'm naked!

43:55.101 --> 43:56.367
Honey?

43:56.369 --> 43:57.269
I mean it, Arnie.

43:57.271 --> 44:00.407
I'm naked, completely naked.

44:00.409 --> 44:02.909
Don't you dare come down
here, and don't you dare

44:02.911 --> 44:05.646
bring some other man down here.

44:05.648 --> 44:07.780
What... what about Wren?

44:07.782 --> 44:09.751
Honey, he's looking for Wren.

44:09.753 --> 44:12.521
Well, she's gone.

44:12.523 --> 44:15.791
I have no idea where she is.

44:15.793 --> 44:17.126
It's OK.

44:17.128 --> 44:22.932
It's... she can call me later.

44:22.934 --> 44:24.768
You can't
make this stuff up.

44:32.246 --> 44:37.615
I am 74 years
old, and not once...

44:37.617 --> 44:41.552
not once... have I had a
police officer enter my home.

44:41.554 --> 44:43.690
Honey, everything's fine.

44:43.692 --> 44:44.391
No, no.

44:44.393 --> 44:46.126
Everything's not fine.

44:46.128 --> 44:48.496
Everything is far from fine.

44:48.498 --> 44:51.898
Driving without a license,
hiding from the police.

44:51.900 --> 44:55.537
Breaking and entering,
conspiring with a...

44:55.539 --> 45:00.108
an ex-con, prisoner, pen
pal, or who knows what.

45:00.110 --> 45:01.476
Everything's not fine.

45:01.478 --> 45:03.177
I never meant to
cause any trouble.

45:03.179 --> 45:04.179
Oh, what did you mean to do?

45:04.181 --> 45:05.113
Honey.

45:05.115 --> 45:06.282
No, I'm just
asking a question.

45:06.284 --> 45:07.083
No, he's... he's right.

45:07.085 --> 45:08.550
You're right.

45:08.552 --> 45:11.923
I... I put you in a
compromising position.

45:11.925 --> 45:14.490
I don't care for people
who have something to hide.

45:14.492 --> 45:15.691
I understand.

45:15.693 --> 45:18.530
My wife and I, we have
been... well, I have been...

45:18.532 --> 45:21.065
a law-abiding
citizen all my life.

45:21.067 --> 45:22.401
Arnie.

45:22.403 --> 45:25.670
So have I. And I know
you might not believe that,

45:25.672 --> 45:26.572
but it's true.

45:31.512 --> 45:33.414
How much do you
know about wrens?

45:33.416 --> 45:36.115
Oh, honey, I don't think
she wants to talk about birds.

45:36.117 --> 45:39.619
No, I think she'll
find this interesting.

45:39.621 --> 45:42.757
Legend has it that
back in the day,

45:42.759 --> 45:45.728
the birds decided to
make whichever bird

45:45.730 --> 45:48.530
flew the highest their king.

45:48.532 --> 45:50.766
So do you know
what the wren did?

45:50.768 --> 45:56.173
The wren hid inside the
feathers of a great eagle.

45:56.175 --> 46:00.344
It hitched a ride
to a great height,

46:00.346 --> 46:03.414
only to emerge and
outfly the eagle

46:03.416 --> 46:06.784
after the eagle had tired.

46:06.786 --> 46:11.557
As a punishment, the wren is now
forced to live a life of shame

46:11.559 --> 46:16.563
in almost total concealment.

46:16.565 --> 46:17.431
Excuse me.

46:21.003 --> 46:22.769
What's wrong with you?

46:25.641 --> 46:27.041
Oh.

46:27.043 --> 46:32.514
What's... what's wrong with me?

46:59.614 --> 47:00.947
Jo.

47:00.949 --> 47:01.849
Don't you touch me.

47:01.851 --> 47:03.050
I'm mad at you.

47:03.052 --> 47:03.684
Look.

47:03.686 --> 47:05.485
No, you look.

47:05.487 --> 47:08.521
How long has it been since we
had a young girl in our lives?

47:08.523 --> 47:09.856
Oh, come on.

47:09.858 --> 47:13.061
No, it's OK for you because
you never do anything wrong.

47:13.063 --> 47:16.664
I'm the one who always
ruins everything.

47:16.666 --> 47:18.300
I want her to like me.

47:18.302 --> 47:23.105
I need to feel like I can
do it right this time.

47:33.686 --> 47:40.592
'Cause when it's
raining, I've no regrets.

47:40.594 --> 47:46.566
Because it isn't
raining rain, you know.

47:46.568 --> 47:48.469
It's raining violets.

47:56.045 --> 48:01.617
And when you see the
clouds up on the hills,

48:01.619 --> 48:07.023
you're gonna see
crowds of daffodils.

48:11.597 --> 48:15.099
I'm sorry.

48:15.101 --> 48:16.000
Me, too.

48:21.074 --> 48:29.081
Sunflower, yellow and gold.

48:29.083 --> 48:39.059
I saw her plant it
beside the road.

48:39.061 --> 48:44.532
I can't take her.

48:44.534 --> 48:47.036
No.

48:47.038 --> 48:54.911
'Cause she's so pretty
beside the road.

49:13.034 --> 49:14.034
Good morning.

49:14.036 --> 49:15.970
Good morning.

49:15.972 --> 49:16.470
How...

49:16.472 --> 49:16.871
Come in.

49:24.280 --> 49:24.679
Huh.

49:28.251 --> 49:29.885
Do you know about the bluejay?

49:32.757 --> 49:39.162
Well, the bluejay is
a very arrogant bird.

49:39.164 --> 49:43.900
Very bratty and, uh, mean.

49:43.902 --> 49:44.869
They intimidate.

49:44.871 --> 49:46.104
They're bullies.

49:46.106 --> 49:48.574
They can get way out of control.

49:48.576 --> 49:51.543
But they do it to
protect their own.

49:51.545 --> 49:54.913
They... they don't
mean it personal.

49:59.989 --> 50:02.456
Yeah?

50:02.458 --> 50:04.925
Yeah.

50:10.467 --> 50:11.967
I liked having them.

50:11.969 --> 50:14.871
I didn't know my lemonade stand
would be such an attraction.

50:27.251 --> 50:27.818
Oh!

50:27.820 --> 50:29.318
Hey!

50:29.320 --> 50:30.287
I, uh...

50:30.289 --> 50:31.755
I was just going
down to the Lemkes.

50:31.757 --> 50:32.758
Oh?

50:32.760 --> 50:34.126
She's not home.

50:38.632 --> 50:39.998
They just fell out.

50:51.880 --> 50:53.749
Mr. Bayberry?

50:53.751 --> 50:55.217
Officer.

50:55.219 --> 50:57.052
You're a bird man.

50:57.054 --> 50:58.619
Ornithologist.

50:58.621 --> 51:02.258
Just got back from an
expedition in Kenya.

51:02.260 --> 51:03.291
What brings you here?

51:03.293 --> 51:04.994
My wife isn't, um...

51:04.996 --> 51:06.362
Oh, no.

51:06.364 --> 51:07.498
Good.

51:07.500 --> 51:11.068
I'm sure that was just,
uh, one of those things.

51:11.070 --> 51:12.070
One can only hope.

51:14.806 --> 51:15.941
No.

51:15.943 --> 51:16.941
I can't.

51:16.943 --> 51:19.344
It's only you and
me in the garage.

51:19.346 --> 51:20.780
Who's gonna know?

51:20.782 --> 51:21.181
OK.

51:26.121 --> 51:28.289
Her name isn't
even on the envelope.

51:28.291 --> 51:29.190
Just the address.

51:29.192 --> 51:29.722
OK.

51:29.724 --> 51:30.791
What is it?

51:30.793 --> 51:31.825
I don't know.

51:31.827 --> 51:33.894
It doesn't start or
stop on this page.

51:33.896 --> 51:35.662
It's in the middle of something.

51:35.664 --> 51:36.530
Read it.

51:36.532 --> 51:37.932
OK.

51:37.934 --> 51:42.137
"I was hoping so much that John
would be here when I returned,

51:42.139 --> 51:46.141
but the only person who
was there was Evelyn.

51:46.143 --> 51:48.711
I was almost shaking,
I was so nervous.

51:48.713 --> 51:51.081
"You know how you play things
over and over in your head

51:51.083 --> 51:53.651
when something doesn't
happen the way you expect?

51:53.653 --> 51:56.320
It's like you're left
wandering in a dream.

51:56.322 --> 51:58.822
Like the other day,
when I was by myself,

51:58.824 --> 52:00.925
doing the simplest of things...

52:00.927 --> 52:03.429
a load of laundry
by the screen door.

52:03.431 --> 52:04.630
And there it was...

52:04.632 --> 52:06.532
his shirt.

52:06.534 --> 52:08.367
And then I just stopped.

52:08.369 --> 52:12.539
I put it down right where it
was and just left the house

52:12.541 --> 52:15.943
with everything scattered."

52:15.945 --> 52:18.711
That's it?

52:18.713 --> 52:19.514
It ends there?

52:22.652 --> 52:24.452
One more?

52:24.454 --> 52:27.222
I was wondering if
you or someone you know

52:27.224 --> 52:31.795
could tell me what
kind of bird this is.

52:31.797 --> 52:32.929
Where'd you find this?

52:32.931 --> 52:35.065
Flew against my window.

52:35.067 --> 52:35.932
I could hear it flapping.

52:35.934 --> 52:38.001
It was stuck against the screen.

52:38.003 --> 52:41.237
Been staring at it ever since
for no particular reason.

52:41.239 --> 52:42.639
Then I remembered
seeing all those bird

52:42.641 --> 52:43.407
pictures at your house.

52:43.409 --> 52:45.342
I thought I'd ask, uh...

52:45.344 --> 52:46.912
This is my photograph!

52:46.914 --> 52:48.345
My picture!

52:48.347 --> 52:49.315
Yours?

52:49.317 --> 52:50.950
I lost it.

52:50.952 --> 52:52.351
This is a pygmy falcon.

52:52.353 --> 52:54.320
A pygmy falcon?

52:54.322 --> 52:55.889
I was in my
front yard going over

52:55.891 --> 53:01.695
photos from my trip when I first
discovered this among the rest.

53:01.697 --> 53:03.863
I don't remember
taking this picture,

53:03.865 --> 53:08.369
and a bird man like me is paid
to remember that sort of stuff.

53:08.371 --> 53:11.072
I might have thought I was crazy
if it hadn't been for Wren.

53:11.074 --> 53:11.874
Your neighbor.

53:11.876 --> 53:13.307
Mm.

53:13.309 --> 53:16.912
Yeah, she was there when I
saw this for the first time.

53:16.914 --> 53:19.316
She knew what it was.

53:19.318 --> 53:21.818
Immediately, which is rare.

53:21.820 --> 53:25.322
She knew exactly what it was.

53:25.324 --> 53:30.128
Do you mind telling
me what you know?

53:30.130 --> 53:32.496
About pygmy falcons?

53:32.498 --> 53:33.798
About wrens.

53:37.103 --> 53:39.472
Oh.

53:39.474 --> 53:43.476
What my wife wouldn't
give to be here now.

53:43.478 --> 53:46.479
"It's not difficult
to say your wife has passed.

53:46.481 --> 53:48.514
The information flows freely.

53:48.516 --> 53:50.818
You can be very
third-person about it,

53:50.820 --> 53:52.987
almost pretend as if it
has happened to someone

53:52.989 --> 53:55.391
you've never met.

53:55.393 --> 53:58.126
What's hard are the...

53:58.128 --> 54:02.599
what's hard are the questions,
the inevitable questions

54:02.601 --> 54:04.800
that come up later.

54:04.802 --> 54:08.305
That's what trips you up."

54:08.307 --> 54:08.706
Wow.

54:15.882 --> 54:17.983
"Have
you watched something dead?

54:17.985 --> 54:19.950
Have you stared it down?

54:19.952 --> 54:23.021
Have you held it in your hands?

54:23.023 --> 54:24.824
Do you know what it looks like?

54:24.826 --> 54:26.592
I do.

54:26.594 --> 54:27.894
Relief."

54:27.896 --> 54:29.929
"And I knew
then it was over for us."

54:29.931 --> 54:34.202
"I actually knew the night
before, when she didn't call..."

54:34.204 --> 54:35.436
"...when she had gone

54:35.438 --> 54:37.905
all weekend with hardly a word.

54:37.907 --> 54:39.641
She always called."

54:39.643 --> 54:42.711
"Without exception."

54:42.713 --> 54:43.979
"So
I went to the bar

54:43.981 --> 54:46.950
where we first me and
listened to jazz like we

54:46.952 --> 54:48.284
used to in the beginning.

54:48.286 --> 54:49.719
Except this time..."

54:49.721 --> 54:52.521
"...I didn't feel inspired.

54:52.523 --> 54:54.825
I fear I have no idea who I am."

54:54.827 --> 54:56.728
I kissed
my grandfather on the cheek

54:56.730 --> 55:00.063
and told him to feel better,
even though I knew it would be

55:00.065 --> 55:01.097
the last time I would ever..."

55:01.099 --> 55:02.200
"I decided

55:02.202 --> 55:04.202
to tell the truth for a change.

55:04.204 --> 55:06.472
Maybe I'm just tired of
trying to be someone else."

55:06.474 --> 55:07.907
"I lifted a hand

55:07.909 --> 55:09.775
to anyone behind bars here.

55:09.777 --> 55:12.010
Almost five years now.

55:12.012 --> 55:13.546
But I feel it coming up."

55:26.963 --> 55:28.496
"They disappeared.

55:28.498 --> 55:30.199
My sister said they
did not come back."

55:30.201 --> 55:31.700
"My mama told me I'd

55:31.702 --> 55:33.503
be pretty when I gold older.

55:33.505 --> 55:37.106
He says he has a friend
who wants to love me, too."

55:56.532 --> 55:58.231
"Listening
to children laughing.

55:58.233 --> 56:00.467
I should be happy hearing
these soft, sweet sounds,

56:00.469 --> 56:03.338
but all I can think about
is how large I've become,

56:03.340 --> 56:06.807
how much I've let myself go.

56:06.809 --> 56:08.177
I'm so fat."

56:08.179 --> 56:09.711
"I'm so unloved.

56:09.713 --> 56:11.313
I have no baby.

56:11.315 --> 56:13.983
These words play
over in my head.

56:13.985 --> 56:16.385
I can hear those
kids playing even

56:16.387 --> 56:19.190
when my ears are underwater.

56:19.192 --> 56:22.325
It's true.

56:22.327 --> 56:25.063
You can hear joy through waves."

56:28.168 --> 56:30.702
Oh god, that's sad.

56:30.704 --> 56:31.536
Don't worry.

56:31.538 --> 56:33.271
I'll put them in a safe place.

56:33.273 --> 56:36.309
Yeah, but what...
what if she finds out?

56:36.311 --> 56:38.811
Something is happening here.

56:38.813 --> 56:41.414
It... it is beyond us.

56:41.416 --> 56:43.617
I mean, I don't
even know here,

56:43.619 --> 56:47.789
and I just can't get
her off of my mind.

56:47.791 --> 56:50.192
Maybe you should
write her a letter.

57:57.237 --> 57:59.104
Hi.

57:59.106 --> 58:01.740
I... I used to play
when I was young.

58:01.742 --> 58:02.442
Nice to see you.

58:05.079 --> 58:06.579
Nice to see you.

58:06.581 --> 58:08.581
You wanna play?

58:08.583 --> 58:09.481
Come on.

58:13.054 --> 58:14.054
Come on.

58:14.056 --> 58:15.456
It's gonna be beautiful.

58:18.561 --> 58:18.960
Thanks.

58:34.012 --> 58:34.411
Yes.

58:38.018 --> 58:40.517
That's so good.

01:00:33.282 --> 01:00:35.115
Where's Arnold?

01:00:35.117 --> 01:00:36.217
He'll be here.

01:00:36.219 --> 01:00:37.952
He's just getting a
refill for the kids.

01:00:53.172 --> 01:00:55.039
Everything all right?

01:01:01.882 --> 01:01:03.682
Oh, Jo.

01:01:03.684 --> 01:01:04.951
Get my camera.

01:01:09.490 --> 01:01:11.224
Look at him.

01:01:11.226 --> 01:01:12.226
Uh-oh.

01:01:12.228 --> 01:01:13.695
He's spilling
the lemonade.

01:01:13.697 --> 01:01:15.095
Jo Jo, get my camera.

01:01:15.097 --> 01:01:15.931
Jo Jo.

01:01:19.335 --> 01:01:20.369
Shh.

01:01:20.371 --> 01:01:21.202
Not a good move.

01:01:21.204 --> 01:01:22.606
I couldn't do that.

01:01:22.608 --> 01:01:23.941
He might not get up.

01:01:27.844 --> 01:01:28.243
Shh.

01:01:31.916 --> 01:01:32.983
Oh my god.

01:01:32.985 --> 01:01:35.653
Easy now.

01:01:35.655 --> 01:01:36.720
Easy, easy.

01:01:36.722 --> 01:01:37.588
Oh!

01:01:37.590 --> 01:01:38.454
Whoops!

01:01:38.456 --> 01:01:39.657
Arnie!

01:01:39.659 --> 01:01:40.391
A what?

01:01:40.393 --> 01:01:43.195
A Bali starling.

01:01:43.197 --> 01:01:46.432
Just sitting there in
my crab apple tree.

01:01:46.434 --> 01:01:50.104
Arnie, one of the most
important and obvious

01:01:50.106 --> 01:01:53.005
characteristics in
identifying a Bali starling

01:01:53.007 --> 01:01:57.177
is, not surprisingly, that it
is typically found in Bali.

01:01:57.179 --> 01:01:57.945
Oh, I know.

01:01:59.016 --> 01:02:00.180
And, more
specifically, in three

01:02:00.182 --> 01:02:03.184
separate bird parks in Bali.

01:02:03.186 --> 01:02:08.757
You do realize that there are
barely over 100 in existence?

01:02:08.759 --> 01:02:10.626
And if you count the
ones in captivity

01:02:10.628 --> 01:02:13.429
or the ones poached for the
cage bird trade, even then...

01:02:13.431 --> 01:02:15.898
No, no, no.

01:02:15.900 --> 01:02:18.001
This was not a caged bird.

01:02:18.003 --> 01:02:19.403
It's not possible.

01:02:19.405 --> 01:02:22.373
It was a Bali starling.

01:02:22.375 --> 01:02:24.275
It was the most
astonishing sighting I

01:02:24.277 --> 01:02:26.512
have ever had in my life ever.

01:02:26.514 --> 01:02:30.483
It's what we wait our
whole lives for is...

01:02:30.485 --> 01:02:31.416
it was a miracle.

01:02:31.418 --> 01:02:35.889
Like
the pygmy falcon.

01:02:35.891 --> 01:02:37.224
Dammit.

01:02:37.226 --> 01:02:40.061
Stan, I am not crazy.

01:02:40.063 --> 01:02:41.327
I know what I saw.

01:02:41.329 --> 01:02:44.097
I saw a Bali starling,
stark white with the blue

01:02:44.099 --> 01:02:45.467
around the eyes.

01:02:45.469 --> 01:02:47.034
And the tuft.

01:02:47.036 --> 01:02:49.037
There's nothing else like it.

01:02:49.039 --> 01:02:50.238
Nothing.

01:02:50.240 --> 01:02:51.641
I saw it.

01:02:51.643 --> 01:02:53.409
I had it in my sights.

01:02:53.411 --> 01:02:57.780
It was 10 feet away from
me for a full minute.

01:02:57.782 --> 01:03:02.920
I had a very, very
good look at it.

01:03:05.791 --> 01:03:07.692
I know what I saw.

01:03:29.954 --> 01:03:33.923
Come to the neighborhood
if you want to see her.

01:03:33.925 --> 01:03:37.092
Sit with us on the lawn.

01:03:37.094 --> 01:03:41.664
There's something quite
special about her.

01:03:41.666 --> 01:03:46.436
Soft-spoken, graceful, elegant.

01:03:46.438 --> 01:03:49.941
She seems tall, even
though she's not.

01:03:52.778 --> 01:03:56.115
Every day she walks.

01:03:56.117 --> 01:04:00.519
It seems simple enough, but
with her it's different.

01:04:00.521 --> 01:04:06.059
It's purposeful, as though
she's walking on air.

01:04:06.061 --> 01:04:07.528
She's so quiet.

01:04:07.530 --> 01:04:11.099
She just appears.

01:04:11.101 --> 01:04:16.104
And before you know
it, she's gone.

01:04:16.106 --> 01:04:18.039
Dispatch
to Officer Burkheart.

01:04:18.041 --> 01:04:21.976
Come in, Officer Burkheart.

01:04:29.853 --> 01:04:31.221
What are you looking at?

01:04:33.893 --> 01:04:38.262
I'm waiting for
the second coming.

01:04:51.246 --> 01:04:57.217
Well, the moon is broken,
and the sky is cracked.

01:04:57.219 --> 01:05:01.688
Come on up to the house.

01:05:01.690 --> 01:05:07.829
The only things that you can
see is all that you lack.

01:05:07.831 --> 01:05:10.666
Well, come on up to the house.

01:05:13.739 --> 01:05:18.641
All your crying
don't do no good.

01:05:18.643 --> 01:05:23.046
Come on up to the house.

01:05:23.048 --> 01:05:26.318
Well, come down off the cross.

01:05:26.320 --> 01:05:28.820
We can use the wood.

01:05:28.822 --> 01:05:32.793
You gotta come on
up to the house.

01:05:32.795 --> 01:05:33.193
Yeah.

01:05:55.152 --> 01:06:01.624
You gotta come on
up to the house.

01:06:01.626 --> 01:06:05.595
Come on up to the house.

01:06:05.597 --> 01:06:08.566
The world is not my home.

01:06:08.568 --> 01:06:10.568
I'm just a-passin' through.

01:06:10.570 --> 01:06:14.940
You've got to come
on up to the house.

01:06:20.983 --> 01:06:21.383
Oh.

01:06:27.356 --> 01:06:30.224
I came to get
the letters back.

01:06:55.255 --> 01:06:57.722
They're in there.

01:06:57.724 --> 01:06:58.123
Oh.

01:07:07.168 --> 01:07:07.601
Thank you.

01:07:10.673 --> 01:07:11.938
Shh.

01:07:11.940 --> 01:07:12.507
Shh.

01:07:12.509 --> 01:07:14.409
It's OK, baby.

01:07:14.411 --> 01:07:16.411
It's just you and me.

01:07:16.413 --> 01:07:16.813
Huh?

01:07:21.353 --> 01:07:23.353
Oh, god, you little beauty.

01:07:23.355 --> 01:07:24.722
What are you doing here?

01:07:28.293 --> 01:07:28.692
Ooh.

01:07:34.766 --> 01:07:35.266
Are you posing?

01:07:37.871 --> 01:07:39.704
I'm sorry about
your granddaughter.

01:07:39.706 --> 01:07:41.440
What?

